'''"-eşti"''' is a widespread [[Romanian language|Romanian]] suffix used indicating a placename, being in fact a plural of the possesive suffix "[[-escu]]", formerly used for [[patronym]]s and currently widespread for family names. An obsolete form is "-esci" or "-eşci", being sometimes used before the beginning of the [[20th century]]. Another form sometimes found is "-ăşti". In some areas in Romania, more than half of the placenames have this suffix.
